03/06/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Deputy Prime Minister Abdullatif Sener announced Friday (June 1st) that he will not run for Parliament in the general elections on July 22nd, confirming recent speculation.
He stressed, though, that his decision does not mark an end to his political career.
A founding member of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP), Sener has been in Parliament since 1991.
Press reports say his announcement may indicate he is a possible presidential candidate.
(Zaman, Turkish Daily News - 02/05/07)
